analysisPopulations.name: All Entered Set Population
analysisPopulations.label: AES
analysisPopulations.description: All patients who sign inform consent and enter in this study
analysisPopulations.criteria: Signed informed consent and entered the study

analysisPopulations.name: All Randomized Set Population
analysisPopulations.label: ARS
analysisPopulations.description: All patients who are randomized to study treatments

analysisPopulations.name: Full Analysis Set Population
analysisPopulations.label: FAS
analysisPopulations.description: All randomized patients who receive at least 1 dose of study drug. This population is used for safety analyses and efficacy analyses other than the primary outcome.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Randomized and received at least 1 dose of study drug

analysisPopulations.name: Efficacy Analysis Set Population
analysisPopulations.label: EAS
analysisPopulations.description: Patients in the FAS and have evaluable primary efficacy outcome
analysisPopulations.criteria: Member of the Full Analysis Set with an evaluable primary efficacy outcome

analysisPopulations.name: PK/PD Population
analysisPopulations.label: PK/PD
analysisPopulations.description: Patients in the FAS and have evaluable PK/PD.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Member of the Full Analysis Set with evaluable Pharmacokinetic/Pharmacodynamic data

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.label: SAF
analysisPopulations.description: All randomized patients who receive at least 1 dose of study drug. Per the SAP, safety analyses are conducted on the Full Analysis Set (FAS).
analysisPopulations.criteria: Randomized and received at least 1 dose of study drug

characteristics.name: Age
characteristics.description: Age of the subject at baseline

characteristics.name: Diabetes Type
characteristics.description: Type of diabetes mellitus (Type 1 or Type 2)

characteristics.name: Duration of Diabetes
characteristics.description: Duration of diabetes in years at baseline

characteristics.name: Baseline Clarke Hypoglycemia Awareness Status
characteristics.description: Hypoglycemia awareness status at baseline, assessed by the Clarke questionnaire

characteristics.name: Previous Diabetic Therapy
characteristics.description: History of previous therapies for diabetes
